external_knowledge:
- "Morbidity" refers to the condition of being diseased, or the incidence of disease within a population; 
- "Nutrition programs" are interventions aimed at improving nutritional outcomes in a target population;
- "Researchers" in this context, are likely individuals who study, design, or evaluate these programs.

sql:
SELECT value
FROM program_evaluations
WHERE program_id = 0 AND year = 2023;

SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM nutrition_programs 
WHERE implementing_agency = 'Ministry of Health';

SELECT AVG(value) AS average_metric_value
FROM program_evaluations
WHERE metric_id = 0;

SELECT program_name, target_population
FROM nutrition_programs
WHERE program_id = 0;

SELECT program_id, COUNT(DISTINCT funding_agency) AS unique_funding_sources
FROM funding_sources
GROUP BY program_id;

SELECT metric_id, AVG(value) AS average_evaluation_value
FROM program_evaluations
GROUP BY metric_id;
